title: John Lee Hooker - Columbia, MD 1992 (SBD) [FLAC]
description:
John Lee Hooker
Vala Cupp
Coast to Coast Blues Band
June 18, 1992
Merriweather Post Pavilion
Columbia, Maryland

Unofficial Soundboard Recording - Excellent Sound Quality


1. Why Baby
2. I Wouldn't Treat A Dog (The Way You Treated Me)
3. Leave My Woman Alone
4. T-R-O-U-B-L-E
5. Instrumental / Band Intros
6. Jailhouse Blues
7. Cold, Cold Feeling
8. A Man Size Job
9. John Lee Hooker Introduction
10. It Serves Me Right To Suffer
11. Same Old Blues Again
12. Hi-Heel Sneakers
13. Boogie Chillen'
14. Outro Jam


Personnel:

John Lee Hooker - guitar, vocals (tracks 9-14)
Vala Cupp - vocals (tracks 6-8)

further lineup Coast To Coast Blues Band:

Mike Osborn - guitar


others unknown - probably:
Melvyn "Deacon" Jones - keyboards
? - bass,
? - drums

Duke Robillard (?) - guitar, vocals (tracks 3 & 4)
Debbie Davies (?) - guitar (tracks 6-8)


Notes: A high class JLH performance - typical for this era of his career. As a warm up the Coast to Coast Blues Band playing some Blues Standards: I Wouldn't Treat A Dog (Bobby 'Blue' Bland), Leave My Woman Alone (Ray Charles), Jailhouse Blues (Lightnin' Hopkins), Cold, Cold Feeling (Albert Collins), A Man Size Job (Denise LaSalle). The sound quality is excellent to perfect. But there was a little confusion about the main info's. I grabbed it from another forum with wrong or lacking song titles - so I corrected them and added tagging. The original info also  postulated Duke Robillard on guitar (tracks 3 & 4) and Debbie Davies on guitar (tracks 6-8). I'm not sure about it. But it's definitely Vala Cupp on vocals (tracks 6-8), who was not credited in the original info sheet. - maxblues
